WEBVTT

00:05.706 --> 00:06.707 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Good
evening. I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:06.707 --> 00:09.309 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:09.309 --> 00:14.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: On the "NewsHour"
tonight: upheaval on campus. The
University of Missouri
chancellor

00:14.448 --> 00:21.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and president step down amid
increasing student and faculty
protests over racism and
representation.

00:21.455 --> 00:27.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead this
Monday: Russia is caught in a
state-sponsored doping scandal,

00:27.127 --> 00:32.165 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
putting Russian athletes in
danger of being banned from the
2016 Olympics.

00:32.165 --> 00:36.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And life on the road
with Gloria Steinem. The famed
activists talks about fighting

00:36.904 --> 00:40.374 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for feminism in a new memoir.

00:40.374 --> 00:44.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM, Author, "My Life
on the Road": It was only after
I had been living this
on-the-road

00:44.111 --> 00:50.717 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
life for quite a long time,
until I was 50, that I realized,
wait a minute, this isn't

00:50.717 --> 00:53.453 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
just something on the way to
something else. This is it.

00:53.453 --> 00:56.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:56.056 --> 01:02.062 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:02.062 --> 01:14.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Students and
faculty members celebrated today
at the main campus of the

01:14.141 --> 01:18.946 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
University of Missouri, after
the head of the university
system quit.

01:18.946 --> 01:23.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Tim Wolfe was accused
of ignoring racial incidents.
The situation reached a

01:23.483 --> 01:29.423 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
boiling point when black
football players announced a
boycott Saturday night. Later,

01:29.423 --> 01:33.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the chancellor overseeing the
main campus also resigned. We
will investigate this story

01:33.627 --> 01:36.530 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
in detail after
the news summary.

01:36.530 --> 01:41.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: A judge in Louisiana
set bail at $1 million apiece
today for two police

01:41.668 --> 01:47.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
officers accused of murdering an
autistic boy. Six-year-old
Jeremy Mardis was killed

01:47.507 --> 01:52.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and his father was wounded when
the officers fired on the
family's vehicle 18 times. A

01:52.746 --> 01:59.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lawyer for the father says
police video shows he had his
hands up when the shooting
started.

01:59.753 --> 02:05.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In Jordan, two
Americans, a South African and
two Jordanians were gunned

02:05.258 --> 02:11.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
down today by a police captain
in Amman. It happened at a
regional police training center.

02:11.198 --> 02:16.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In addition to the dead, seven
people were wounded, including
two more Americans. The

02:16.570 --> 02:20.741 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gunman was shot and killed by
soldiers. U.S. officials said
the Americans were security

02:20.741 --> 02:24.678 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
contractors training
Palestinian police.

02:24.678 --> 02:28.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Washington, President Obama
promised an investigation.

02:28.148 --> 02:32.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States: We take this very
seriously and we will be

02:32.686 --> 02:39.626 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
working closely with the
Jordanians to determine exactly
what happened. But, at this
stage,

02:39.626 --> 02:45.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to just let everyone to
know that this is something we
are paying close attention

02:45.098 --> 02:52.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to, and at the point where the
families have been notified,
obviously, our deepest
condolences

02:52.339 --> 02:54.674 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will be going out to them.

02:54.674 --> 02:59.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The president spoke
during an Oval Office meeting
with Israeli Prime Minister

02:59.379 --> 03:03.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Benjamin Netanyahu. The
relationship has been strained
since the Iran nuclear deal that

03:03.817 --> 03:06.253 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Israel opposed.

03:06.253 --> 03:10.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Netanyahu insisted he's
still committed to Middle East
peace.

03:10.924 --> 03:16.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BENJAMIN NETANYAHU, Israeli
Prime Minister: We have not
given up our hope for peace. We

03:16.463 --> 03:20.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will never give up our hope for
peace. I don't think that anyone
should doubt Israel's
determination

03:20.801 --> 03:25.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to defend itself against terror
and destruction, but neither
should anyone doubt Israel's
willingness

03:25.872 --> 03:31.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to make peace with any of its
neighbors that genuinely want to
achieve peace with it.

03:31.678 --> 03:35.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Still, the White
House said it no longer expects
peace can be achieved before

03:35.482 --> 03:39.686 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mr. Obama leaves office
in January 2017.

03:39.686 --> 03:45.425 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Israel also
joined those saying a bomb
destroyed that Russian airliner
over

03:45.425 --> 03:49.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Sinai Peninsula. The Israeli
defense minister said -- quote
-- "There is a high probability

03:49.429 --> 03:52.199 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it was a bombing."

03:52.199 --> 03:58.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, evacuation flights
resumed for Russian tourists
stranded in Sinai. About

03:58.805 --> 04:04.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
23,000 have flown home since
Saturday. Cargo planes are
transporting their luggage
separately.

04:04.478 --> 04:10.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Greenhouse gas
levels hit an all-time high last
year. The U.N. Weather Agency's

04:10.317 --> 04:16.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
report today comes amid -- comes
ahead of a world summit on
climate change. The report

04:16.256 --> 04:23.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
says carbon dioxide levels are
now more than 140 percent higher
than before the Industrial

04:23.563 --> 04:28.435 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Revolution. The amount of
methane is up 250 percent since
that same period. And the report

04:28.435 --> 04:32.005 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
forecasts another
increase next year.

04:32.005 --> 04:37.577 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back in this
country, a federal bankruptcy
judge OKed a reorganization plan

04:37.577 --> 04:43.550 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
for the Roman Catholic
Archdiocese of Milwaukee. It
stems from damage claims over
sexual abuse

04:43.550 --> 04:51.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by priests. The plan calls for
paying a total of $21 million to
nearly 460 victims.

04:51.191 --> 04:56.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Wall Street had a
blue Monday over worries about
the global economy. The

04:56.429 --> 05:03.537 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dow Jones industrial average
lost nearly 180 points to close
at 17730. The Nasdaq fell

05:03.537 --> 05:08.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
nearly 52 points. And the
S&amp;P 500 was down 20.

05:08.008 --> 05:14.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And SeaWorld says
that it will phase out its
killer whale shows in San Diego

05:14.648 --> 05:21.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by 2017. Instead, the theme park
will focus on the animals'
natural setting and behavior.

05:21.488 --> 05:26.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The announcement follows growing
criticism of the treatment of
killer whales in captivity.

05:26.526 --> 05:31.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SeaWorld has seen attendance
plummet as a result. The
company's decision doesn't apply

05:31.064 --> 05:35.969 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to its other theme parks that
include killer whale shows.

05:35.969 --> 05:41.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
the University of Missouri
president ousted over his
handling

05:41.274 --> 05:46.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of racial issues; Russia's
involvement in widespread
steroid use; addressing Mexico's

05:46.813 --> 05:53.653 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
diabetes epidemic,
and much more.

05:53.653 --> 06:06.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: It's been an
eventful day in Columbia,
Missouri, where the university
has been the

06:06.933 --> 06:11.605 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
center of national attention
over racial tensions on campus.

06:11.605 --> 06:15.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the heart of the protest was
a hunger strike that resonated
across the campus and across

06:15.242 --> 06:17.377 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the state.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM WOLFE, President, University
of Missouri: I am resigning as
president of the University

06:19.679 --> 06:22.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Missouri system.

06:22.182 --> 06:25.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The announcement
from Tim Wolfe came right after
the university system's
governing

06:25.485 --> 06:28.755 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
body opened a special meeting.

06:28.755 --> 06:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM WOLFE: This is not, I
repeat, not the way change
should come about. Change comes

06:40.400 --> 06:50.577 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from listening, learning, caring
and conversation. Unfortunately,
this has not happened, and

06:50.577 --> 06:56.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is why I stand before you
today. And I take full
responsibility for this
frustration,

06:56.316 --> 07:02.822 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and I take full responsibility
for the inaction that has
occurred.

07:02.822 --> 07:08.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Wolfe's resignation
followed months of complaints
over racial slurs on the
overwhelmingly

07:08.128 --> 07:14.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
white campus at Columbia,
including a swastika drawn on a
dormitory wall with human feces.

07:14.734 --> 07:17.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The student government president
was one of the targets.

07:17.871 --> 07:20.774 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAYTON HEAD, President, Missouri
Students Association: What
happens here is that they

07:20.774 --> 07:24.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have the opportunity to create
an environment that is
inclusive, that you can put in
place

07:24.678 --> 07:30.583 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a zero tolerance policy for acts
of bias and discrimination on
this campus.

07:30.583 --> 07:36.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: As protests grew,
Wolfe's car was blocked during a
homecoming parade, black

07:36.189 --> 07:41.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
graduate student Jonathan Butler
began a hunger strike,
protesting the slurs and the
overall

07:41.161 --> 07:44.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
racial climate at the
state university.

07:44.197 --> 07:49.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The tipping point arrived this
weekend, when at least 30 black
football players announced

07:49.235 --> 07:54.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
they would boycott team
activities until Wolfe was
removed.

07:54.107 --> 07:59.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Head coach Gary Pinkel endorsed
the protest, posting a photo of
the team locking arms,

07:59.012 --> 08:04.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying, "We are united." By
today, faculty members were
pledging to join in.

08:04.784 --> 08:12.592 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The season of academic
discontent is not limited to
Missouri. At Yale, students and
administrators

08:12.592 --> 08:18.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have also been thrust into
campus upheaval, as a memo over
appropriate Halloween costumes

08:18.064 --> 08:24.003 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
triggered longstanding tensions
about race and free speech.

08:24.003 --> 08:29.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Columbia, Tim Wolfe's
resignation exposed raw nerves
about the lack of diversity
among

08:29.075 --> 08:34.781 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
students and faculty, while also
showcasing the muscle of the
school's athletic department.

08:34.781 --> 08:39.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As students celebrated, Jonathan
Butler declared his hunger
strike over.

08:39.052 --> 08:41.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN BUTLER, Student,
University of Missouri: It
should not have taken this much.
And it

08:41.721 --> 08:45.692 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is disgusting and vile that we
find ourselves in the place that
we do.

08:45.692 --> 08:51.164 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Also, the football
players announced they are
returning to practice tomorrow.

08:51.164 --> 08:56.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Earlier this evening, before the
chancellor also resigned, I
spoke to Brenda Smith-Lezama,

08:56.803 --> 09:00.573 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the vice president of the
student body at the university
of Missouri, and Scott Brooks,

09:00.573 --> 09:04.110 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
an associate professor
of sociology.

09:04.110 --> 09:09.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Brenda Smith-Lezama, you have
been in the middle of this and
you know what the conversations

09:09.315 --> 09:14.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have been. How much relief is
there tonight or how much
concern is there still in the

09:14.654 --> 09:17.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wake of this protest?

09:17.223 --> 09:19.125 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA, Vice
President, Missouri Students
Association: Well, the relief is

09:19.125 --> 09:20.827 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
unsurmountable.

09:20.827 --> 09:25.498 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, at the same time, it's just
a first step. And that's the one
thing that I think all

09:25.498 --> 09:30.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
students involved in this
movement want to reiterate. This
is not the endgame. So, we

09:30.603 --> 09:34.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
need to think about how we're
going to move forward and
proceed with the administration,

09:34.140 --> 09:36.810 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as well as involving students.

09:36.810 --> 09:41.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Professor Brooks, is
this a new issue that we're
hearing so much about now

09:41.314 --> 09:45.151 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or is it an old one that's
been given new life?

09:45.151 --> 09:47.854 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT BROOKS, Associate
Professor, University of
Missouri: No, it's definitely an
old one

09:47.854 --> 09:50.957 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that has been given new life.

09:50.957 --> 09:57.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can go back to 1969 with the
Legion of Black Collegians and
them giving a list of

09:57.630 --> 10:04.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
demands of their concerns at
that time. And so whether we're
talking about 1969 here at

10:04.003 --> 10:08.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the University of Missouri or
whether we're talking about
other campuses, I think that

10:08.908 --> 10:15.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's a fairly common story for
black students, even black
faculty staff, that they are
operating

10:15.615 --> 10:21.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on -- at a university and they
have this kind of mixed feeling.

10:21.087 --> 10:25.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, it's a place where
they're coming to get the best
that they can from the
university.

10:25.959 --> 10:30.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are looking and hoping and
expecting that this is the time
of their lives, and

10:30.597 --> 10:36.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
yet they are stuck -- struck
with a harsh reality, that
they're not treated often as

10:36.169 --> 10:40.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
equal citizens, as equal
students, and that's across the
levels, faculty, staff and
students.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.843 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So this is not a new story.

10:43.843 --> 10:49.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Brenda Smith-Lezama,
tell me how a little bit what --
how this blew up, how

10:49.582 --> 10:53.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this became such a big issue,
and whether this has been your
personal experience, the

10:53.920 --> 10:57.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stories that we're now hearing
coming out of campus about the
experiences of black students

10:57.891 --> 11:00.159 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
not only now, but
for some time now.

11:00.159 --> 11:03.129 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA:
Well, of course.

11:03.129 --> 11:07.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, I think that, for most
students, there has been a shift
post-Ferguson and going back

11:07.834 --> 11:13.072 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to that year, year-and-a-half
period, the activism on campus
has been at an all-time

11:13.072 --> 11:18.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
high. I think that, for the
first time, movements were being
led in a very systematic and
very

11:18.478 --> 11:22.148 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
intentional manner.

11:22.148 --> 11:27.921 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, coming from the student
body, I think that there is a
lot of change that we all

11:27.921 --> 11:30.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
see that needs to be made, and
this is the first time that we
have all been able to rally

11:30.189 --> 11:33.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
around one cause, and that
is making them do better.

11:33.426 --> 11:36.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, this is a
post-Ferguson effect, as it
were?

11:36.462 --> 11:39.699 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA:
Absolutely. Absolutely.

11:39.699 --> 11:44.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that, at least for me, I
will say that, prior to Ferguson
and all the events

11:44.437 --> 11:50.743 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that followed, there was
obviously racial issues and
there was a lot of issues of
systematic

11:50.743 --> 11:56.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
oppression with itself. However,
after Ferguson was -- one, we
were met with a lot of silence

11:56.816 --> 12:00.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from our administration. And I
think what is most frustrating,
is that when students

12:00.153 --> 12:03.923 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were crying out for help, our
administration left us stranded.

12:03.923 --> 12:07.560 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, let me ask you
this. And then I want to ask
Professor Brooks as well.

12:07.560 --> 12:12.632 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What difference will it make
that president Wolfe is gone, if
this is a question and a

12:12.632 --> 12:18.104 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
problem that's predated even
his arrival on campus in 2012?

12:18.104 --> 12:23.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA: Removing
Tim Wolfe is by no means going
to solve the system that

12:23.810 --> 12:27.447 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has built for so many years here
at the University of Missouri.

12:27.447 --> 12:33.987 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
However, I think that
specifically after Ferguson, Tim
Wolfe did serve as kind of the
icon of

12:33.987 --> 12:38.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the system that has failed us.
And one of the biggest things
that students have brought

12:38.658 --> 12:43.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up with concern is the fact that
we need to have educators in
those positions, people

12:43.930 --> 12:47.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who are willing to make that
change, people who are willing
to listen to students, rather

12:47.634 --> 12:53.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than meet us with silence and
not validate our concerns and
our struggles.

12:53.873 --> 12:56.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Professor Brooks,
what about that? What difference
will it make if the president

12:56.843 --> 12:59.846 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the university is now gone?

12:59.846 --> 13:06.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT BROOKS: Well, I think that
Brenda has articulated it very
well.

13:06.119 --> 13:13.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is simply a step in the
right direction. The difference
is not about removing Tim Wolfe.

13:13.393 --> 13:16.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The difference is going to be
seen in what happens next. And
that's really what we're

13:16.829 --> 13:20.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
encouraged to pay attention to.

13:20.967 --> 13:26.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, what we're excited
about is, how can we move
forward, now that we know that

13:26.105 --> 13:31.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there is at least one less
person that we feel has been an
obstacle? This is the way

13:31.010 --> 13:37.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that students feel. And this is
also a way that faculty, staff
are coming together. We're

13:37.350 --> 13:43.723 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
coming together under the guise
of, you know, what are -- what
changes can we make now that

13:43.723 --> 13:48.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we have at least an opportunity
for shared government?

13:48.361 --> 13:51.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You know, I want to
go to what happens next, but
allow me for -- going back

13:51.330 --> 13:56.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for a moment, would this have
reached the head it did,
starting with you, Professor

13:56.469 --> 14:00.807 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Brooks, if there had not been
the involvement of the student
athletes, of the football team?

14:00.807 --> 14:02.508 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Was that the tipping point?

14:02.508 --> 14:05.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT BROOKS: Right.

14:05.344 --> 14:13.219 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, I think that you have to
look at the student athlete and
their student side. So,

14:13.219 --> 14:17.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
if the student athlete could not
connect with this larger student
movement, the student

14:17.990 --> 14:21.928 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
athlete wouldn't
necessarily come forward.

14:21.928 --> 14:28.234 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I agree that there is no doubt
the importance of sport is --
you know, we know how important

14:28.234 --> 14:34.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sport has become, particularly
at the university. We call
athletics the front porch of the
university,

14:34.373 --> 14:40.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
talk about the collegiate arms
race, the sports industrial
complex. There was $1 million
that

14:40.480 --> 14:45.318 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the university could occur in
terms of fines if the student
athlete didn't perform, if

14:45.318 --> 14:48.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the football players did
not go out onto the field.

14:48.621 --> 14:54.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so there is no doubt that
that is an important
consideration for each and every
university

14:54.494 --> 14:59.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that has a big football -- a
big-time football team. So,
that's not simply a Missouri
issue.

14:59.265 --> 15:05.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's a national issue. And
student athletes have had this
power and they have been trying

15:05.505 --> 15:10.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to exercise this in different
ways for the last couple of
years, as we have seen student

15:10.810 --> 15:16.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
athletes organizing around
amateurship vs. being able to
gain some stipends.

15:16.916 --> 15:24.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So this is a growing national
piece as well. The revolt of the
athlete has never gone too

15:24.190 --> 15:29.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
far beneath the surface. It did
take a moment like this and the
courage of our concerned

15:29.629 --> 15:34.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
students to step forward to help
to galvanize and give student
athletes even a voice and

15:34.901 --> 15:38.070 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a platform and strength
to move forward.

15:38.070 --> 15:42.108 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: And, Brenda
Smith-Lezama, so you have had
today's victory. You admit --
you

15:42.108 --> 15:46.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
concede that it's a partial
victory. So what does happen
next?

15:46.345 --> 15:51.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA: Well,
honestly, I'm a student. I am
not an administrator. I am not

15:51.284 --> 15:55.354 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the one who is paid and tasked
with coming up with these
answers.

15:55.354 --> 15:59.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's the one thing that
has been so frustrating over the
past year-and-a-half,

15:59.292 --> 16:04.664 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is that administrators have
often held back and asked us to
come up with the solutions.

16:04.664 --> 16:08.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can't go to school full-time,
work and then on top of that do
an administrator's job as

16:08.968 --> 16:12.071 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
well. And that's
what's so crucial.

16:12.071 --> 16:17.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I will say is that this, if
nothing else, really put our
administrators on high alert

16:17.109 --> 16:20.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to know that University of
Missouri students will not stand
idly by and let our university

16:20.780 --> 16:23.182 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
fall to pieces.

16:23.182 --> 16:26.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Brenda Smith-Lezama,
vice president of the student
body at University of Missouri,

16:26.919 --> 16:29.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and Professor Scott Brooks,
thank you both very much.

16:29.655 --> 16:34.594 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT BROOKS: Thank you.

16:34.594 --> 16:43.469 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRENDA SMITH-LEZAMA:
Thank you for having us.

16:43.469 --> 16:48.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now allegations
that Russian athletes have been
gaming international sports

16:48.674 --> 16:51.377 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for years.

16:51.377 --> 16:57.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A report out today from an
independent commission of the
World Anti-Doping Agency found
-- quote

16:57.183 --> 17:02.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- "a deeply rooted culture of
cheating in Russia's track and
field programs, including

17:02.722 --> 17:07.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
systemic doping, bribery and
destruction of evidence, much of
it done at the Russian
government's

17:07.126 --> 17:10.162 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
behest."

17:10.162 --> 17:15.134 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The commission's report
recommended lifetime bans for
five Russian runners, including
the

17:15.134 --> 17:20.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gold and bronze medal winners
at the 2012 London Olympics.

17:20.773 --> 17:24.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Commission head Richard Pound
said the doping had to be
state-sponsored.

17:24.343 --> 17:27.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD POUND, Chairman, World
Anti-Doping Agency: Our
conclusion was that all of this

17:27.713 --> 17:34.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
could not have happened or
continued to happen without the
knowledge of and either actual

17:34.320 --> 17:39.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or implied consent of the state
authorities. They were not
operating the sport, but, as

17:39.425 --> 17:45.898 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I say, they would certainly have
known, and could not not have
known about this.

17:45.898 --> 17:48.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let's take a
deeper look into the
investigation and its impact
with a sports

17:48.968 --> 17:52.738 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
reporter who has long
covered the Olympics.

17:52.738 --> 17:57.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Christine Brennan of USA Today
is also a commentator for ABC
News, and she joins me now.

17:57.243 --> 17:58.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Welcome back to the
program, Christine.

17:58.978 --> 18:01.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, this is an extraordinary
report, isn't it?

18:01.414 --> 18:03.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN, USA
Today: Well, it is.

18:03.149 --> 18:06.819 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's groundbreaking and it's
earth-shattering in many ways,
although, for those who have

18:06.819 --> 18:11.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been watching what's happened
with FIFA, the soccer governing
body, and all the concerns

18:11.257 --> 18:15.361 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there -- and people may go back
and remember the East Germans
and the cheating in swimming

18:15.361 --> 18:19.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and track and field all the way
back to the '60s and into '70s,
that in some ways this

18:19.198 --> 18:22.635 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
may not shock people at all.

18:22.635 --> 18:29.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But here we are talking about
one of the great forces in
Olympic sports, Russia, of
course,

18:29.008 --> 18:33.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just hosted the last Olympic
Games, the Winter Olympics,
which Vladimir Putin paid $51
billion

18:33.879 --> 18:34.413 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to put on.

18:34.413 --> 18:36.582 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

18:36.582 --> 18:40.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: And now to
have this story hit, in many
ways no surprise, and yet
obviously

18:40.686 --> 18:43.456 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
eye-opening and very alarming.

18:43.456 --> 18:47.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And when you
start to read this report,
Christine, you see, it's not

18:47.059 --> 18:50.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
only the athletes, it's the
coaches, it's the doctors, it's
the people who regulate

18:50.896 --> 18:53.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the sport, and, as we said,
going all the way up to the
government.

18:53.532 --> 18:54.834 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Exactly.
The government is implicated.

18:54.834 --> 18:59.538 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, you know, I don't know that
we will ever get to the bottom
of exactly how high up this

18:59.538 --> 19:05.845 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
goes in Russia, but I think we
can dream big. And when you
think of how important the Sochi

19:05.845 --> 19:11.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Olympics were to Putin and to
Russia and the kind of money
that they spent in that country

19:11.250 --> 19:14.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at this time with so many
issues, you just have to wonder
if it goes all the way to the

19:14.653 --> 19:16.889 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to.

19:16.889 --> 19:21.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as I said, we will never
know. And, journalistically, we
have no idea right now. But what
the World

19:21.861 --> 19:28.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Anti-Doping Agency is alleging
here is extraordinary. And if it
starts to work people up and
sponsors

19:28.234 --> 19:30.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up to what's really going on in
some of these countries, then I
think it turns out to be

19:30.970 --> 19:33.139 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a good thing.

19:33.139 --> 19:37.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is it possible to
put on a finger on how many --
who won and who didn't

19:37.943 --> 19:41.881 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
win, who medaled and who didn't
as a result of this cheating?

19:41.881 --> 19:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Oh, in some
ways. You alluded to the fact
that the gold and the bronze
medal

19:44.417 --> 19:47.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the women's 800 meters
would be taken away.

19:47.620 --> 19:51.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think fans over the years have
come to realize, for example,
with Lance Armstrong, when they

19:51.490 --> 19:56.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stripped away his titles, seven
Tour de France titles, that
there was only one person in

19:56.262 --> 20:02.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the three times seven, 21 of the
top three in each seven years,
who would have been clean.

20:02.368 --> 20:06.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so going back to the Olympic
record books in the '70s, where
we know the East Germans

20:06.238 --> 20:09.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the Soviets were cheating,
and then you still look at their
records and you still

20:09.975 --> 20:13.612 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
look at their names as
medalists, so, in some way,
that's almost a futile effort
because

20:13.612 --> 20:16.882 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it's so much bigger than that.

20:16.882 --> 20:20.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it certainly is sad for
those athletes who haven't
cheated to be denied those
medals.

20:20.920 --> 20:24.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now, we should
point out the Russian
government, Russian officials
are

20:24.090 --> 20:27.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
saying that this is politically
motivated. They are denying it.

20:27.860 --> 20:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Among other things, they're
saying that how can you accuse
them of doing this when the

20:34.800 --> 20:38.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
international agency was in
charge of doing the testing?
They're saying, if we were doing

20:38.971 --> 20:41.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this, then why didn't
somebody see it at the time?

20:41.741 --> 20:43.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Well, and
it's a good point, except for
this, that the Russian officials

20:43.809 --> 20:46.378 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
run those labs.

20:46.378 --> 20:50.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So the lab was in Sochi. And, of
course, this does bring into
question what was going on

20:50.382 --> 20:54.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at the Sochi Olympics. Right
now, we're talking track and
field athletes. And, obviously,

20:54.487 --> 20:57.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that is a huge sport for the
Summer Games, and whether these
athletes and whether Russia

20:57.590 --> 21:00.092 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should even be allowed to have
track and field athletes in Rio
next summer.

21:00.092 --> 21:01.727 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

21:01.727 --> 21:05.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: But you go
back to Sochi, which of course
was this hub of international

21:05.397 --> 21:11.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sports based on the Winter
Olympics, and those officials
there are running that lab.

21:11.570 --> 21:16.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also keep in mind that Russian
security officials were
involved, and there are the
implications

21:16.175 --> 21:19.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and allegations that they were
actually strong-arming some of
these people to make these
decisions

21:19.678 --> 21:24.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or to in some cases destroy
up to 1,400 drug tests.

21:24.550 --> 21:28.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Christine, just
quickly, another argument that
is heard today is that, well,

21:28.888 --> 21:31.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this is going on in a lot of
places, it's not just the
Russians. How much validity is

21:31.023 --> 21:32.591 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there?

21:32.591 --> 21:34.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Oh, I think
it's true. And I think, when we
look at baseball, look

21:34.593 --> 21:37.796 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at all of our sports in the
United States, to think that the
bad chemists, Judy, are

21:37.796 --> 21:40.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
still way ahead of
the good chemists.

21:40.566 --> 21:44.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, drug testing is important,
but they can't catch all the
designer drugs that are being

21:44.637 --> 21:50.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
made that they haven't yet found
a test for. So I think the
important thing for fans and

21:50.376 --> 21:54.880 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people who love sports, buyer,
beware. As a consumer, you know
that that product could

21:54.880 --> 21:58.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be tainted, whether it's Major
League Baseball, the NFL, any
sport in the United States
potentially,

21:58.651 --> 22:00.920 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but also at the Olympic level.

22:00.920 --> 22:03.989 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, finally,
just quickly, effect on the
Olympics going forward?

22:03.989 --> 22:07.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Yes. I think
it has a big effect, because
when you look at the tainted

22:07.593 --> 22:11.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nature of this and the fact that
if people can't trust what
they're watching, if you

22:11.630 --> 22:15.801 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can't trust a foot race between
eight men or eight women, what
in the world can you

22:15.801 --> 22:18.771 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
trust and how does that impact
sponsors moving forward?

22:18.771 --> 22:23.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Christine
Brennan, it's quite a story.

22:23.542 --> 22:28.314 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN:
Thank you, Judy.

22:28.314 --> 22:32.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thank you.

22:32.384 --> 22:36.288 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Take care.

