malls and big box stores with
abundant shelves, and an
epidemic of diabetes.

23:16.462 --> 23:19.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAVIER LOZANO, Clinicas del
Azucar: Regular food, but sugar
free.

23:19.832 --> 23:24.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Javier
Lozano, whose mother suffers
from the disease, thinks he can
make

23:24.003 --> 23:28.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a difference. Three years ago,
he opened a chain called
Clinicas del Azucar, or the
Sugar

23:28.374 --> 23:30.509 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Clinics.

23:30.509 --> 23:34.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAVIER LOZANO: Our dream was,
imagine there's a clinic in
every corner. Just as we have

23:34.713 --> 23:39.551 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
franchise for hamburgers and
pizza and fried chicken.

23:39.551 --> 23:43.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The clinics
are a one-stop shop to see a
doctor or nutritionist, get

23:43.656 --> 23:48.594 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
your eyes checked, or feet, then
pick up a pair of shoes or
snacks.

23:48.594 --> 23:55.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lozano, a 33-year-old MIT
graduate, hopes to have 200
outlets by 2020, but it's a tiny

23:55.534 --> 24:01.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fraction of the demand in a
country that by then could have
20 million diabetics.

24:01.173 --> 24:05.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SIMON BARQUERA, National
Health Institute: Basically,
diabetes prevalence has been
doubling

24:05.577 --> 24:08.514 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
every six to 10 years.

24:08.514 --> 24:13.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Dr. Simon
Barquera of Mexico's National
Health Institute says it

24:13.719 --> 24:18.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now affects 14 percent of
Mexican adults, a population
with widespread genetic
predisposition

24:18.290 --> 24:21.627 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to diabetes.

24:21.627 --> 24:26.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Adding to the risk, 72 percent
are obese or overweight. Those
numbers are now higher than

24:26.999 --> 24:31.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mexico's northern neighbors, but
with double the impact. Far
fewer Mexicans have their

24:31.337 --> 24:34.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
symptoms under control.

24:34.073 --> 24:38.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. SIMON BARQUERA: For example,
in Canada and the U.S., more
than half of the population

24:38.243 --> 24:41.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with diabetes has adequate
control, in Mexico, only 25
percent.

24:41.747 --> 24:47.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Complicating
matters, half of those affected
aren't aware they have

24:47.052 --> 24:51.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
diabetes. And those who are
diagnosed can remain
asymptomatic for years, and they
do

24:51.056 --> 24:54.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
little to control its advance.

24:54.126 --> 24:58.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SIMON BARQUERA: They go
looking for private care and
they see that it's too
expensive.

24:58.931 --> 25:06.472 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, usually, they go back to
the public care, and it's
limited. So, you know, when

25:06.472 --> 25:11.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people have a difficult
decision, we usually just defer
the decision.

25:11.877 --> 25:18.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Maria De La
Luz Mireles (ph) says she
struggled for years with
scattered,

25:18.117 --> 25:22.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
substandard care until
specialists at the Sugar Clinic
helped bring her symptoms under

25:22.287 --> 25:24.356 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
control.

25:24.356 --> 25:28.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIA DE LA LUZ MIRELES, Mexico
(through translator): I went to
many clinics and never got to
see

25:28.727 --> 25:32.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a specialist. It was general
doctors and they'd change my
medications. This went on for 20

25:32.965 --> 25:35.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

25:35.033 --> 25:40.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: That overall
lack of access to care means
more advanced cases: limb
amputations,

25:40.939 --> 25:46.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
heart, kidney and eye disease,
more people like Luis Martinez,
at 64, long retired and

25:46.512 --> 25:48.814 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
nearly incapacitated.

25:48.814 --> 25:54.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LUIS MARTINEZ, Diabetes Patient
(through translator): My kidneys
have been very seriously
affected,

25:54.186 --> 25:58.724 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so I have to have dialysis twice
a day, and four months ago, I
lost the last bit of sight

25:58.724 --> 26:00.959 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that I had.

26:00.959 --> 26:05.731 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: As a young
man, Martinez moved from the
country to the city, part of

26:05.731 --> 26:11.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a massive urbanization. Three
out of four people now inhabit
cities in this once agrarian

26:11.270 --> 26:16.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
nation, says Sugar Clinics
endocrinologist Eduardo Camacho.

26:16.008 --> 26:20.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. EDUARDO CAMACHO, Clinicas
del Azucar (through translator):
Most people lived in the
countryside,

26:20.179 --> 26:25.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and so they used a lot of energy
and got a lot of exercise in
order to feed themselves.

26:25.317 --> 26:29.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was labor-intensive work.
Now, with urbanization, people
are using much less energy in
their

26:29.588 --> 26:32.991 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
daily lives to get the
food that that they need.

26:32.991 --> 26:40.065 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Then there's
the food, plentiful, affordable,
but processed. Dr.

26:40.065 --> 26:44.837 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Barquera says it's an
industrialized version of the
healthy, traditional Mexican
diet.

26:44.837 --> 26:50.042 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EDUARDO CAMACHO: What we have
now, tacos, both the tortillas,
bigger. They have a lot

26:50.042 --> 26:54.613 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of meat. They have a lot of fat.
Sometimes, the quesadillas are
deep-fried.

26:54.613 --> 26:59.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): People
are on the go, working, so if
you have got money, you

26:59.284 --> 27:02.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
go to a restaurant. If you
don't, you eat tacos on the
street. And people drink soda,

27:02.988 --> 27:05.324 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
rather than have water.

27:05.324 --> 27:10.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Maria
Sanchez Perez, who is losing her
sight and lives in fear of a

27:10.829 --> 27:14.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
stroke, blames her
addiction to Coca-Cola.

27:14.266 --> 27:17.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARIA SANCHEZ PEREZ, Diabetes
Sufferer (through translator):
Those big bottles that you see,

27:17.202 --> 27:19.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
those wouldn't even
last me a day.

27:19.371 --> 27:25.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She's hardly
alone. According to Coca-Cola,
Mexicans are far and away the

27:25.210 --> 27:31.016 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
biggest consumers of the
company's products, especially
the flagship Coca-Cola, which is

27:31.016 --> 27:36.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sold in three-liter bottles in
this country. On average, the
company says Mexicans consume

27:36.221 --> 27:42.494 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
43 gallons of Coke products per
year. That works out to about 55
of these per person

27:42.494 --> 27:46.031 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
per year.

27:46.031 --> 27:54.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2014, after a campaign by
citizen activist groups, Mexico
became the first nation to

27:54.706 --> 28:00.078 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
enact a so-called soda tax, 10
percent on sugar-sweetened
drinks, 8 percent on salty

28:00.078 --> 28:06.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
snacks. In its first year, one
study showed consumption dropped
by 6 percent. But the

28:06.218 --> 28:10.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
study's methods were questioned
by the food and beverage
industry, led by multinationals

28:10.422 --> 28:14.293 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
including U.S.- based
Coke and Pepsi.

28:14.293 --> 28:18.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The industry has fought such tax
proposals, successfully in most
cases, including New

28:18.330 --> 28:20.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
York and San Francisco.

28:20.566 --> 28:24.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LORENA CERDAN, Mexican Consumer
Products Industry Board: It's a
regressive...

28:24.369 --> 28:24.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: It's a
regressive tax, is what you're
saying.

28:24.169 --> 28:26.405 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORENA CERDAN: It's a
regressive tax, yes.

28:26.405 --> 28:31.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Lorena
Cerdan is a spokesperson for
Mexico's food and beverage trade
group,

28:31.209 --> 28:36.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which argues its products
are unfairly singled out.

28:36.148 --> 28:42.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's absolutely no link
between soda consumption at 43
gallons per person per year and
the

28:42.854 --> 28:46.158 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
disease burden of this country?

28:46.158 --> 28:51.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LORENA CERDAN (through
translator): There is no causal
relationship to link directly

28:51.897 --> 28:56.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sugary drinks with diabetes.
There is a causal relationship
between a sedentary lifestyle

28:56.134 --> 28:59.004 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and an overconsumption
of calories.

28:59.004 --> 29:03.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She says the
urbanized lifestyle and overall
increase in calories

29:03.075 --> 29:10.248 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
from many sources
are the problem.

29:10.248 --> 29:14.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The industry has contributed to
public awareness and fitness
campaigns. But its critics, like

29:14.486 --> 29:18.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
consumer advocate Alejandro
Calvillo, are skeptical.

29:18.123 --> 29:23.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEJANDRO CALVILLO, Consumer
Advocate: They are, by this way,
trying to create confusion,

29:23.895 --> 29:30.902 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that you don't have good
products or bad products.
Everything is on the relation of
the calorie

29:30.902 --> 29:34.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
intake that you consume and
the calories that you spend.

29:34.506 --> 29:39.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He says
there's also been lackluster
enforcement of recent
regulations,

29:39.244 --> 29:43.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
banning salty snacks and sodas
in schools, for example.

29:43.148 --> 29:47.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAVUTO: All right. This is the
schools in the country that we
have reports that are

29:47.719 --> 29:52.124 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not following the regulation. We
are making a list of the
schools.

29:52.124 --> 29:56.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: And experts
say it's not just at school, but
at home that a culture

29:56.261 --> 30:04.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shift is needed; 26-year-old
Karla Almanza gets good grades
from her nutritionist at

30:04.169 --> 30:09.341 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the Sugar Clinics for
controlling her weight and sugar
levels. But she says its not
been

30:09.341 --> 30:14.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
easy cutting out foods and
sugary drinks she loves and
imposing a diet on her mother,
who

30:14.613 --> 30:18.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is also diabetic, and two
daughters and her husband, who
are not.

30:18.984 --> 30:22.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KARLA ALMANZA, Diabetes Sufferer
(through translator): For the
children, I have always

30:22.888 --> 30:27.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cooked like that. They're used
to it. It's really difficult for
my husband. He says:

30:27.025 --> 30:30.495 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
"I'm not a rabbit. Give
me some more meat."

30:30.495 --> 30:35.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: It's also
hard on the budget, she says.
The healthy diet, ironically,

30:35.600 --> 30:41.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is costlier than fast food.
Helping her budget, her clinic
fees are fixed, payable up front

30:41.940 --> 30:46.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the full year, though
financing is offered to help
patients afford care.

30:46.678 --> 30:51.516 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Lozano says this ensures
patients come back regularly,
their complications not only
treated,

30:51.516 --> 30:53.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but also tracked.

30:53.752 --> 30:58.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAVIER LOZANO: We have been on
the -- more than three years in
care and we have seen

30:58.223 --> 31:02.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more than 15,000 patients.
So we have a lot of data.

31:02.194 --> 31:06.298 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The data
helps determine what works and
what doesn't, which also in

31:06.298 --> 31:11.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
turn helps lower costs and
increase access to care in an
epidemic that most experts says

31:11.002 --> 31:14.506 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this nation is unprepared for.

31:14.506 --> 31:19.411 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," this is
Fred de Sam Lazaro in Monterrey,
Mexico.

31:19.411 --> 31:23.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Fred's reporting is
a partnership with the
Under-Told Stories Project at
Saint

31:23.415 --> 31:29.554 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Mary's University of Minnesota.

31:29.554 --> 31:41.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We turn now to
Asian nation of Myanmar, the
country formerly known as

31:41.266 --> 31:46.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Burma, where Sunday's election
is on track to produce a
landslide victory to the party

31:46.104 --> 31:50.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of former political
prisoner Aung San Suu Kyi.

31:50.075 --> 31:54.312 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We start with a report from John
Irvine of Independent Television
News.

31:54.312 --> 32:01.987 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN IRVINE: It seems the world
has a new democracy. After years
of brutal repression,

32:01.987 --> 32:06.892 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Burma's freedom movement and its
charismatic leader, Aung San Suu
Kyi, have prevailed,

32:06.892 --> 32:11.363 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and that was something to
celebrate here tonight.

32:11.363 --> 32:18.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: She is genius. She is
genius. She is a great leader.
She is very honest. She is

32:18.804 --> 32:22.073 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
like father. She is our mother.

32:22.073 --> 32:29.481 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN IRVINE: But the day began
differently, with Yangon
strangely subdued. Many heeded

32:29.481 --> 32:35.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
official advice to stay at home.
The joy of yesterday's vote had
been replaced by uncertainty

32:35.053 --> 32:38.590 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about what might happen next.

32:38.590 --> 32:44.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, when election officials
didn't show up to announce
results at the appointed time,

32:44.930 --> 32:51.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there was concern that democracy
delayed might be democracy
denied again.

32:51.403 --> 33:00.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Soon, Ms. Suu Kyi appeared at
her party headquarters. She
urged supporters to keep calm
and to remain

33:00.912 --> 33:06.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
peaceful. Then, nine hours late,
the first results did come in,
and people were calm

33:06.985 --> 33:09.087 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
no more.

33:09.087 --> 33:13.158 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

33:13.158 --> 33:24.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN IRVINE: Not long ago, just
being a member of this political
party was a jailable offense.

33:24.035 --> 33:28.139 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Aung San Suu Kyi served a total
of 15 years in custody. Now the
former prisoner is poised

33:28.139 --> 33:29.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to become (INAUDIBLE)

33:29.474 --> 33:35.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the five years since Ms. Suu
Kyi's release, many new faces
have turned up here, businessmen

33:35.447 --> 33:41.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and tourists for whom part of
the appeal of this place is its
timeless quality. The flip

33:41.319 --> 33:47.158 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
side is that many Burmese
live in a time forgot.

33:47.158 --> 33:54.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Slums like this are commonplace.
Home is a tiny stilted shack
teetering over swampland.

33:54.799 --> 34:00.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These are the people Aung San
Suu Kyi has promised to help.
Ms. Suu Kyi's next burden

34:00.238 --> 34:07.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is expectation. But after
decades of struggle, she has put
herself in a position to
deliver.

34:07.279 --> 34:14.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democracy has won through here,
a thrilling prospect for people
impatient for a future.

34:14.619 --> 34:19.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we take a
closer look at Myanmar's
historic election with Tom
Malinowski.

34:19.958 --> 34:23.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's the assistant secretary of
state for democracy, human
rights and labor.

34:23.828 --> 34:26.264 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to the program.

34:26.264 --> 34:26.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI, U.S. Assistant
Secretary of State for
Democracy, Human Rights and
Labor:

34:26.164 --> 34:28.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

34:28.066 --> 34:30.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, is the
opposition win clear? Is there
any doubt that they on the track

34:30.201 --> 34:31.803 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to victory?

34:31.803 --> 34:35.941 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI: Well, we don't
have the official results yet.

34:35.941 --> 34:42.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's important to remember
that, under the system in Burma,
the military is reserved

34:42.147 --> 34:47.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to 25 percent of the seats in
Parliament, which means her
party, the NLD, would have

34:47.652 --> 34:52.357 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to win two-thirds of the
contested seats in order to get
a majority and to form a
government.

34:52.357 --> 34:54.659 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So we don't know if they
have done that yet.

34:54.659 --> 34:57.329 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Does it appear --
some of the early reporting
indicates that it looks like

34:57.329 --> 34:59.364 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that's where they're headed.

34:59.364 --> 35:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI: Well, I don't
want to make predictions as to
numbers.

35:02.600 --> 35:09.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think what -- it is important
to step back, though, and to
remember that this was a day

35:09.307 --> 35:14.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
25 years in coming. A lot of
people in Burma sacrificed and
many died to get to this day.

35:14.813 --> 35:21.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the United States, for all
of that period of time,
supported the hope, the dream
that

35:21.553 --> 35:26.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one day the Burmese people would
be able to make the choice that
they did today.

35:26.624 --> 35:31.796 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there are still enormous
problems. Burma is not yet a
full-fledged democracy, but I

35:31.796 --> 35:36.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
think this does show us that
where we are principled and
patient and persistent in
pursuit

35:36.668 --> 35:39.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of that goal, we can
make a difference.

35:39.571 --> 35:45.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, if Ms. Suu
Kyi's party does obtain the
two-thirds that you just
described,

35:45.043 --> 35:48.880 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
