in this early celebrating.

37:43.361 --> 37:48.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI: Well, it looks
to me like, when people were in
the privacy of the voting

37:48.433 --> 37:54.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
booth, after all of these years
of waiting for this day, they
saw a choice between the

37:54.539 --> 37:59.110 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
past and the future, and despite
everything that has happened and
everything that has

37:59.110 --> 38:02.881 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been said, it looks like most
Burmese are focused on moving
forward.

38:02.881 --> 38:06.184 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, in the next
few days, Secretary Malinowski,
what does the United States look

38:06.184 --> 38:08.953 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for? What are you looking
for to come out of Burma?

38:08.953 --> 38:12.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI: Well, first, we
want to wait and see what the
election observers say about

38:12.457 --> 38:16.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
