of political

38:26.337 --> 38:28.606 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
transition.

38:28.606 --> 38:34.946 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, depending on the results, we
will want to see that the
military, as you suggested,

38:34.946 --> 38:41.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will respect them, will allow a
civilian government to be
formed, and ultimately that
those civilians

38:41.352 --> 38:45.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will have control, and that the
military will gradually step
back and play a more appropriate

38:45.456 --> 38:47.926 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
role for a democratic country.

38:47.926 --> 38:49.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Assistance
Secretary Tom Malinowski, thank
you.

38:49.093 --> 38:53.898 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TOM MALINOWSKI: Thank you.

38:53.898 --> 39:10.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
