45:05.436 --> 45:07.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it came out in his
2010 Senate race.

45:07.638 --> 45:10.474 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And it should be
said, both of them have been on
e-mail raising money.

45:10.474 --> 45:11.642 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: Raising
money off of this.

45:11.642 --> 45:12.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Oh, yes.

45:12.076 --> 45:12.810 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And it's always...

45:12.810 --> 45:15.012 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: The
media is after me.

45:15.012 --> 45:20.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And, as you said,
there is something about the
scrutiny, that it happens every

45:20.217 --> 45:24.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
single election. So is the
attack on the media: Give me
money because the media is
unfairly

45:24.322 --> 45:26.324 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
maligning me.

45:26.324 --> 45:29.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: And Ben Carson
said that, in just last week,
while the media was going

45:29.627 --> 45:33.331 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after him, he raised $3.5
million from 10,000 people.

45:33.331 --> 45:35.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Throw me in the
briar patch, right? It's like,
oh, this is so terrible what
you're

45:35.433 --> 45:35.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
doing to me.

45:35.833 --> 45:36.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

45:36.000 --> 45:37.301 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AMY WALTER: Yes.

45:37.301 --> 45:39.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: The perils
of front-runner-itis.

45:39.103 --> 45:42.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's talk about the Democrats
for a while, because one of the
interesting things we're

45:42.273 --> 45:47.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
seeing happening with Hillary
Clinton and Bernie Sanders in
particular is daylight is

45:47.044 --> 45:50.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happening -- is opening between
these two candidates, who
promised -- at least he had

45:50.581 --> 45:53.818 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
promised that he wasn't really
interested in attacking Hillary
Clinton.

45:53.818 --> 45:55.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: I still don't think
he's interested in attacking
Hillary Clinton.

45:55.553 --> 45:57.021 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Really?

45:57.021 --> 46:04.128 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: No, I mean, when you
see him go on the offense, it's
still very light. And

46:04.128 --> 46:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's still very much about,
listen, I'm just going to put
myself out here. I leave it for

46:09.033 --> 46:12.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you to judge whether or not
Hillary Clinton's been as
consistent.

46:12.837 --> 46:20.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, look, to Hillary Clinton's
credit, she keeps moving further
and further on to Bernie

46:20.144 --> 46:27.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sanders' terrain and moving
further and further to the left.
He's not giving her easy
openings.

46:27.151 --> 46:30.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What he has to make is the
argument that she's not been
consistent in her support, as
opposed

46:30.888 --> 46:34.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to she doesn't support
certain issues.

46:34.392 --> 46:37.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Yes. He seems to
be making the argument that: I
was right all along. I was

46:37.662 --> 46:39.897 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
right first.

46:39.897 --> 46:44.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He doesn't say her name. And he
doesn't actually see this as an
attack. He sees this as fair

46:44.301 --> 46:45.636 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
game, drawing a contrast.

46:45.636 --> 46:47.371 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Comparison, yes.

46:47.371 --> 46:50.708 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Comparison. He
thinks that's completely fair.

46:50.708 --> 46:56.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that his campaign would
like him to push harder, but
he's just not quite as
comfortable

46:56.981 --> 47:02.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with it. And Hillary Clinton has
really no need to overtly go on
the attack against Bernie

47:02.887 --> 47:03.888 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Sanders.

47:03.888 --> 47:06.090 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Only a
few seconds left.

47:06.090 --> 47:09.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have got another debate, yet
another debate tomorrow night.
What are you watching for?

47:09.360 --> 47:14.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Let's see about the
Ben Carson scrutiny and where we
go with that. He's certainly

47:14.198 --> 47:16.434 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
going to be much -- it's
much more of a focus.

47:16.434 --> 47:18.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And Donald Trump has
certainly been going out of his
way to remind everybody

47:18.703 --> 47:21.138 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of what all the questions are.

47:21.138 --> 47:23.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Yes. And all eyes
on Marco Rubio. Will he have
another strong performance in

47:23.107 --> 47:23.808 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this debate?

47:23.808 --> 47:25.976 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: OK.

47:25.976 --> 47:28.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, we will be watching, or
something. I will let you watch
and tell me all about it.

47:28.412 --> 47:29.146 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

47:29.146 --> 47:30.648 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: The next
time we see you, yes.

47:30.648 --> 47:39.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Amy Walter, Tamara
Keith, thank you very much.

47:39.123 --> 47:44.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Thanks.

47:44.195 --> 47:51.635 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: She is a writer,
editor, but, above all, a
feminist activist.

47:51.635 --> 47:55.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gloria Steinem has been in the
forefront of the women's
movement in this country for
more

47:55.506 --> 48:01.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than half-a-century. Now at 81,
she has penned her memoir, "My
Life on the Road," our newest

48:01.579 --> 48:04.648 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
addition to the
"NewsHour" bookshelf.

48:04.648 --> 48:09.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She talked to Jeffrey Brown
recently at the historic
Sewall-Belmont House and Museum
of

48:09.754 --> 48:13.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the women's suffrage and equal
rights movement here in
Washington.

48:13.357 --> 48:18.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You write here
early on about your father, who
taught you something through

48:18.028 --> 48:22.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his -- quote -- "ability to live
with and even love insecurity."

48:22.700 --> 48:25.136 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's an interesting trait.

48:25.136 --> 48:27.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM, Author, "My Life
on the Road": Well, it certainly
was necessary for a freelance

48:27.938 --> 48:31.976 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
writer like me, but I didn't
know that at the time.

48:31.976 --> 48:35.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I just thought that that's the
way life was. And he always
said, "If I don't know what's

48:35.713 --> 48:38.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going to happen tomorrow,
it could be wonderful."

48:38.482 --> 48:43.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And that became
your life in a sense, or
something you could live by?

48:43.087 --> 48:45.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Well, not quite,
because, of course, you want to
be like the other kids,

48:45.823 --> 48:46.557 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you know?

48:46.557 --> 48:48.459 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

48:48.459 --> 48:51.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: So, I looked at
the movies and I saw how kids
went to school and fathers

48:51.428 --> 48:54.265 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
had jobs.

48:54.265 --> 49:01.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And -- but my parents were kind
and loving and wonderful people,
so I was lucky in that

49:01.572 --> 49:06.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
way. And I, of course, didn't
know yet that the idea of living
with insecurity would be

49:06.811 --> 49:12.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
really helpful in later life,
both as a writer and a person in
movements.

49:12.550 --> 49:16.987 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You write a book
about life on the road. When you
look back now, does

49:16.987 --> 49:22.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it look like it was a life that
you chose? Or did it just
happen, unfold?

49:22.927 --> 49:25.029 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: You know,
that's a deep question.

49:25.029 --> 49:26.163 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Good.

49:26.163 --> 49:28.232 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

49:28.232 --> 49:34.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: I think both,
because what we grow up with
feels like home. So, in that

49:34.371 --> 49:38.175 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sense, it was destined.

49:38.175 --> 49:44.481 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I also spent all the middle
years of my life assuming that I
would have to settle

49:44.481 --> 49:49.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
down and live like everybody
else. And it was only after I
had been living this on-the-road

49:49.386 --> 49:55.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
life for quite a long time, I
mean, until I was 50, that I
realized, wait a minute,

49:55.993 --> 49:57.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this isn't just something on the
way to something else. This is
it.

49:57.895 --> 49:58.896 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: This is it.

49:58.896 --> 49:59.997 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Yes, right.

49:59.997 --> 50:01.065 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: This
is who you are.

50:01.065 --> 50:01.799 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: Yes.

50:01.799 --> 50:03.701 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Sure.

50:03.701 --> 50:08.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: And that --
well, I think, in a real way,
because my father had no home,

50:08.038 --> 50:15.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, he was a total wanderer,
and my mother had no journey of
her own, because she had

50:15.479 --> 50:19.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to give up the career as a
writer and a journalist, and,
you know, she kind of gave up
everything

50:19.216 --> 50:21.352 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
she loved.

50:21.352 --> 50:27.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it took me while to realize
that it isn't either/or. It's
and.

50:27.324 --> 50:32.196 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What about today?
Do you see the same commitment,
the same focus in young

50:32.196 --> 50:33.464 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
women?

50:33.464 --> 50:37.501 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: Oh, yes,
more, way, way, way more.

50:37.501 --> 50:43.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were like 12 crazy ladies in
the beginning. You know, we were
definitely the core of
something,

50:43.974 --> 50:50.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but not the something. And now
all of these issues are majority
issues. And young women

50:50.047 --> 50:54.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are way more likely to just
assume that they are going to be
likely to use all of their

50:54.285 --> 50:57.655 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
human talents.

50:57.655 --> 51:02.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, they get radicalized as
they get older, because they get
into the labor force,

51:02.860 --> 51:05.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and they discover that maybe
equal pay is not happening.

51:05.629 --> 51:08.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, the idea that
we're in a post-feminist
society?

51:08.732 --> 51:09.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: Oh,
that's ridiculous.

51:09.400 --> 51:11.302 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Ridiculous.

51:11.302 --> 51:14.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Ridiculous. You
know who's saying that? I can
guarantee you they're the

51:14.638 --> 51:20.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
same people who were saying to
me in the beginning, you can't
do this. It's against God,
Freud,

51:20.844 --> 51:21.612 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
somebody.

51:21.612 --> 51:23.881 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

51:23.881 --> 51:30.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: And now the new
form of obstructionism is to
say, well, it's over, you know,
just

51:30.187 --> 51:31.822 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
to keep you from
doing anything more.

51:31.822 --> 51:34.491 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's so just begun.

51:34.491 --> 51:37.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The book tells
about many successes along the
way. I'm wondering about what
you

51:37.561 --> 51:40.230 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
think of as the
greatest failures.

51:40.230 --> 51:42.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: The confidence
to tell the truth about our
lives.

51:42.766 --> 51:44.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Meaning?

51:44.668 --> 51:49.506 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Well, for
instance, one in three American
women has needed at some time

51:49.506 --> 51:56.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in her life an abortion. And
there's still enough shame to
it, or, you know, controversy

51:56.547 --> 52:01.318 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at least, so that it's difficult
for people to say that.

52:01.318 --> 52:05.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: When you look at
things like abortion rights,
outlawing discrimination

52:05.689 --> 52:12.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the workplace, a lot of
successes along the way, but,
even now, on the defensive in

52:12.129 --> 52:16.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
some areas, right, as these
battles unfold in statehouses.
They continue to unfold.

52:16.133 --> 52:19.970 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Well, yes.

52:19.970 --> 52:25.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Essentially, the people who are
against reproductive freedom
kind of lost what they wanted in
Washington,

52:25.843 --> 52:30.781 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
so now they are striving to
gain it in state legislatures.

52:30.781 --> 52:35.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But opponents of
these things -- and this has
been the case for all your

52:35.719 --> 52:40.858 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
life, I'm sure -- come to these
issues with the same certainty
that you do, the same sense

52:40.858 --> 52:43.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of being right as you.

52:43.994 --> 52:50.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Well, but here's
the difference. We are
protecting their rights.

52:50.501 --> 52:55.339 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We are protecting --
reproductive freedom protects
the right to have children. They

52:55.339 --> 52:59.510 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are not protecting our right to
decide when and whether to have
children.

52:59.510 --> 53:04.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let me ask you,
finally, are you able to imagine
yourself as a young woman

53:04.548 --> 53:07.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in today's society? You're with
young women all the time. You're
still talking to them.

53:07.951 --> 53:08.118 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: Yes.

53:08.118 --> 53:08.919 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

53:08.919 --> 53:10.888 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What advice
do you give to them?

53:10.888 --> 53:13.390 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Here's my
advice: Do not listen to me.

53:13.390 --> 53:14.058 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

53:14.058 --> 53:15.225 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: Really.

53:15.225 --> 53:16.593 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Do not?

53:16.593 --> 53:19.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GLORIA STEINEM: No.

53:19.363 --> 53:25.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I want to support their
listening to themselves. Each of
them has things that they love,
things

53:25.369 --> 53:29.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they do that they love so
much, they forget what time it
is, which is a good measure,

53:29.373 --> 53:33.143 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
when they're doing it.

53:33.143 --> 53:39.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They know their own life and
situations. I'm here to support
that and say, OK you're --
you're

53:39.750 --> 53:42.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not -- OK, you're not more
important than somebody else,
but you're not less important

53:42.753 --> 53:43.821 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
either.

53:43.821 --> 53:46.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right,
"My Life on the Road."

53:46.290 --> 53:47.057 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
Gloria Steinem,
thank you so much.

53:47.057 --> 53:48.492 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GLORIA STEINEM: Thank you.

53:48.492 --> 53:51.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You don't find a lot
of people who will say, "Do not
listen to me," after

53:51.895 --> 53:53.363 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
all this time on
the public stage.

53:53.363 --> 53:55.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You sure don't.

53:55.299 --> 53:57.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Boy, she's been fighting those
battles all this time, but still
-- still seems to have

53:57.601 --> 53:58.335 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the energy to keep fighting.

53:58.335 --> 53:59.937 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Yes.

53:59.937 --> 54:02.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
